<L>__{exterior the grand ticino night}
<A>__{rose and perry emerge from the restaurant.}
<C>__{perry}
<D>__{may i walk with you a ways?}
<C>__{rose}
<D>__{sure.}
<A>__{they set off to the left.}
<L>__{exterior the castorini house night}
<A>__{the door opens, and the old man comes out, in his great coat and hat, with the five dogs. he strikes off to the right.}
<L>__{exterior street i night}
<A>__{rose and perry come around a corner and pass a store. they pause and look at the christmas decorations in the window. they continue walking.}
<L>__{exterior street ii night}
<A>__{the old man and the dogs have stopped by a big tree. which the dogs adore.}
